data.title: A wonderful quick meal in a clean comfortable setting.
data.text: We were walking around downtown Fargo and decided to stop for dinner at the Smiling Moose. We were pleasantly surprised with the cleanliness and very helpful service. The sandwiches and soups were great. It was wonderful to have a dinner out that didn't feel like fast food. I would highly recommend this location for a great meal. Our only complaint is that we were unfamiliar with the term cowboy pickles...they are jalapenos, this is probably something that should be made a little more clear on menus.

data.title: Fresh and good
data.text: Went for breakfast and had morning moose as a breakfast burrito.  Very good.  I was only one there on a Saturday morning.   Enjoyed it!

data.title: Great Sandwiches
data.text: Love the food. I like to create my own sandwiches, better soup selections would be great though. Cookies are great.

data.title: Good sandwiches!
data.text: I like this place if I'm looking for a sandwich that isn't a sub. The bread is great and the ingredients always are fresh,

data.title: Fresh and fast
data.text: Just wanted something quick while sightseeing and liked the name. Was not disappointed as the Wild Turkey and Mt Club sandwiches were great and fast made at the counter.

data.title: Great Food
data.text: Smiling Moose has great sandwiches and soups. I love its downtown location in Fargo, it's an easy place to stop during downtown events.

data.title: Good basic food
data.text: Fast casual restaurant with sandwiches, soups, salads.  They have all-day breakfast sandwiches and skillets.  Staff were friendly and helpful.

data.title: Very good sandwiches!
data.text: I eat at the downtown location for lunch, their sandwiches are excellent. The best thing I love is the Coke free style! Not super cheap but it's worth the price! The service is really good too.

data.title: Good food
data.text: This place is great! For the price, the sandwiches are not very large but are good. Service is only okay. Will return as is one of family favorites! Both 45th and downtown locations are good!

data.title: Big! Fat! Sandwiches!
data.text:
The downtown Fargo location of the Smiling Moose Deli is the only one we visited so far, so we can't say anything about their 45th street location.

That being said, the wife and I stopped in here about a week ago for a late afternoon lunch. I ordered 'The Motherlode', a humongous sandwich stuffed with roast beef, turkey, ham, bacon, and cheese. It had all the usual lettuce, tomatoes, onions, and banana peppers. I asked for the lemon mayo and that was no problem at all.

My wife ordered the locally famous Italian sandwich, which also was packed with cappicola, ham, pepperoni and all the accompaniments. 

Both sandwiches were totally filling to the point that we could only eat half. Of course we brought the other halves home for later!

Although Smiling Moose is a little pricier than other sandwich shops, you definitely get your money's worth.

Very good food. In fact, they could possibly be the best sandwich joint in all of Fargo.

data.title: Awesome Sandwiches
data.text: I used to go here during my work breaks. The sandwiches are nothing short of amazing and the breakfast food is fantastic.

data.title: Hands down the best sandwich I have EVER eaten.
data.text: Hands down the best sandwich I have EVER eaten. The staff was excellent and the food was phenomenal. I would absolutely eat here every time I'm in the Fargo area. WE stumbled upon it by accident as most business's on Broadway are closed on Sundays. We were walking around and found it on a side street to Broadway. Soup was excellent as well. You won't be sorry you stopped!

data.title: IMPECCABLE FOOD
data.text: I've only tried the Harvest wrap and philly cheesesteak but both are amazing every time I get them.  Parking is frustrating for this restaurant but that's Fargo's fault not SMD's.

data.title: We left smiling too!
data.text: I had the Morning Moose, a breakfast sandwich on their gluten free baguette. Eggs, cheese choice of meats, enough to share! But I ate the whole thing! Great selection of Tea Source Teas. Friendly staff, varied seating sunny in front window, quiet in the back. We'll return!

owner_response.text: Thanks Wanda. Tell your friends about us. We would love to meet them! And remember...every Wednesday we give away FREE fresh baked cookies with your salad, wrap or large sandwich so it is always a great day to bring them in and give them the gift of great food:)

data.title: Excellent Cesar's Salad!
data.text: Great Cesar's salad.  I love it.  The soups are good too.  But my favorite definitely are the salads, this was the best place I found for salads.

owner_response.author: everson65, Owner at Smiling Moose Rocky Mountain Deli, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Our salad selection is about to get a whole lot better! Over the next couple of months we are rolling out an expanded salad menu with entirely new offerings. You can also feel free to customize your own salad from our large list of ingredients and diverse dressing options. Either way we hope to see you in again soon!

data.title: So Many Choices Make This a Lunchtime Favorite
data.text: Smiling Moose is conveniently located downtown. Menu choice is very diverse, prices are reasonable, and the food is fantastic.  Service is excellent, too.  Eat in, eat at sidewalk tables (in the summer, of course) or takeout.

owner_response.author: everson65, Owner at Smiling Moose Rocky Mountain Deli, responded to this review
owner_response.text: What?!? You don't want to join us on the patio in the middle of a January blizzard? What could possibly go wrong? :)
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Trendy, enjoyed the fare
data.text: We recently dropped into the Smiling Moose Deli in Fargo, North Dakota. We ordered sandwiches and found that although the service was a bit slow, the food was delicious. The servers are friendly and the decor is interesting, but having Wall Street Journals out was a bit of a puzzlement as the place is much more "New Age" than business-like.

owner_response.author: everson65, Owner at Smiling Moose Rocky Mountain Deli, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thank you for the great review Bill. We would be the first to admit that our food is not the fastest in Fargo...though that is not always our goal. Quality first, speed second:) All the things in life worth doing are worth doing right! In all seriousness though it is always are target to have your food out to you in 5-7 minutes. As for the Wall St. Journal I just love to read it personally so I keep copies at the deli. We also have many sports magazines, travel & leisure, and a book exchange. A little something for everyone. See you soon!
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Great Soup & Sandwich!!!
data.text:
Try the house "Tomato Basil" soup and the 1/2 Rueben w/ coleslaw! A Great combo for a reasonable price. Consistently Good!
Quick & friendly service.

owner_response.author: everson65, Owner at Smiling Moose Rocky Mountain Deli, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Hi JC. Thank you very much for taking the time to leave us a stellar review about your experience last week at the downtown Smiling Moose. We love it when our guests go out of there way to rave about the food. I hope your experience with the staff was pleasant as well. Come see us again soon and bring some friends in on the secret. Give the gift of great food:)

data.title: Gluten free hoagies!
data.text: I had one of their breakfast sandwiches, the Morning Moose, on a gluten free bun. Very good, especially if you are starved because it is big! Friendly staff, helpful with advice.  We have been there several times and had no problems! Great teas also!
